data.name: multiUserCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value:
What is multi-user mode:
You can run all methods in subscription for specified users. Specified users stand for all of them in the dropdown list.
To run batch check the checkbox and:
1. Type user names and passwords - they will be added to the list. 2. Set parameters for methods (they all will be kept). 3. Run 4. Check Usage Statistics in Admin UI and running report.
On Search Tab the multi-user mode will run same search requests for all specified users.
In multi-user mode there will be a separate thread created for each user and all subscribed methods will be run one by one.
Users' threads work in parallel.
Once the batch is run and while it is running, you may uncheck multi-user checkbox and work with this tool as usual.

data.name: bytesCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Check to show first N symbols from method response, otherwise the size of downloaded data is shown in bytes.
The value of the option is that you can quickly check if response contains data or error message.
